type="user">jms-013B</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-013B.xml</fr:route><fr:title
text="On performance trade-offs">On performance trade-offs</fr:title></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Switching to datalog makes forests that make heavy use of queries a bit slower to render. We considered this trade-off carefully, but believe that for the long-term health of Forester, this is acceptable. In the near future, Forester will render trees on demand rather than all at once (except when you are preparing a static archive for upload/deployment); in this mode of use, Forester will be faster than ever.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
