text="Forester 5.0 [TBA] › tl;dr: migration guide"><fr:link
href="jms-011P.xml"
title="Forester 5.0 [TBA]"
addr="jms-011P"
type="local">Forester 5.0 [TBA]</fr:link> › tl;dr: migration guide</fr:title></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>To migrate your forest to <fr:link
href="jms-011P.xml"
title="Forester 5.0 [TBA]"
addr="jms-011P"
type="local">Forester 5.0 [TBA]</fr:link>, do the following:</fr:p><fr:ol><fr:li>Optionally, add a <fr:code>host = "myforestname"</fr:code> line to your <fr:code>forest.toml</fr:code> (see <fr:link
href="jms-011Q.xml"
title="Forester 5.0 [TBA] › a URL scheme for tree addresses"
addr="jms-011Q"
type="local">§ <fr:contextual-number
addr="jms-011Q" /></fr:link>).</fr:li>
  <fr:li>Remove all usage of <fr:code><![CDATA[\transclude/title]]></fr:code> and <fr:code><![CDATA[\transclude/taxon]]></fr:code> (see <fr:link
href="jms-011T.xml"
title="Forester 5.0 [TBA] › removing transclusion overrides"
addr="jms-011T"
type="local">§ <fr:contextual-number
addr="jms-011T" /></fr:link>).</fr:li>
  <fr:li>In your <fr:code>forest.toml</fr:code> file, change the <fr:code>root = "xxx-NNNN"</fr:code> line to <fr:code>home = "xxx-NNNN"</fr:code>, where <fr:code>xxx-NNNN</fr:code> is the name of the tree that you wish to be routed to <fr:code>index.xml</fr:code> (see <fr:link
href="jms-0125.xml"
title="Forester 5.0 [TBA] › renamed root to home"
addr="jms-0125"
type="local">§ <fr:contextual-number
addr="jms-0125" /></fr:link>).</fr:li>
  <fr:li>Any <fr:code><![CDATA[\author]]></fr:code> or <fr:code><![CDATA[\contributor]]></fr:code> attributions must take a tree address as their argument; when you wish to attribute a resource to a person who is not represented by a tree, you can use <fr:code><![CDATA[\author/literal{Somebody’s Name}]]></fr:code> or <fr:code><![CDATA[\contributor/literal{Somebody’s Name}]]></fr:code> (see <fr:link
href="jms-012N.xml"
title="Forester 5.0 [TBA] › Changes to attribution links"
addr="jms-012N"
type="local">§ <fr:contextual-number
addr="jms-012N" /></fr:link>).</fr:li>
  <fr:li>Take into account the renaming of several built-in relations (see <fr:link
href="jms-013C.xml"
title="Forester 5.0 [TBA] › new datalog-based query engine › renamed built-in relations"
addr="jms-013C"
type="local">§ <fr:contextual-number
addr="jms-013C" /></fr:link>).</fr:li>
  <fr:li>Begin rewriting any queries to use the new datalog engine (see <fr:link
href="jms-013A.xml"
title="Forester 5.0 [TBA] › new datalog-based query engine"
addr="jms-013A"
type="local">§ <fr:contextual-number
addr="jms-013A" /></fr:link>), as the legacy query engine will be removed in a subsequent release.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>Begin dialing back your use of custom XML stylesheets (see <fr:link
href="jms-0127.xml"
title="Forester 5.0 [TBA] › the future of Forester’s XML format"
addr="jms-0127"
type="local">§ <fr:contextual-number
addr="jms-0127" /></fr:link>). It is possible that support for customisation at this level will be removed in a future release; if you have innovative customisations that are very important for your use of <fr:link
href="jms-005P.xml"
title="Forester"
addr="jms-005P"
type="local">Forester</fr:link>, consider discussing them on the <fr:link
href="mailto:~jonsterling/forester-discuss@lists.sr.ht"
type="external">mailing list</fr:link> so that maintainers can better understand the problems you are solving.</fr:li></fr:ol></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
